issues.description: The `getNumberOfStudentsPerTutor()` method is specified in the UML and problem text to return a `double`, but in the solution repository it is declared to return an `int`. This signature mismatch will prevent students from matching the expected return type (and from compiling against tests expecting a `double`).
issues.suggested_fix: Change the method signature in both template and solution to `public double getNumberOfStudentsPerTutor()` and update the implementation to return a double, e.g., `(double) getTotalNumberOfStudents() / getNumberOfTutors()`.
